<subsection xml:id="subsec-Constructing-angle-60-30-15">
        <title>Geometrical construction of <m>60^\circ, 30^\circ, 15^\circ, 7.5^\circ</m></title>

        <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-60">
            <title>constructing <m>60^\circ</m></title>
            <activity>
               <figure>
                    <caption></caption>
                    <interactive xml:id="geogebra-angle-60" geogebra="z5mzq6vz" width="100%" aspect="9:5" reset-icon="yes" />
               </figure>

               <figure>
                    <caption></caption>
                    <interactive xml:id="geogebra-angle-60-1" geogebra="sa4uv9pg" width="100%" aspect="10:7" reset-icon="yes" />
               </figure>
            </activity>
            <activity>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Work in pairs
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        What you need: A ruler, a protractor and a pair of compasses.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Explore
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        1.Draw a straight line and mark a point <m>O</m> on it as shown below.
                    </p>

                    <image source="/l4.png" width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                    <p>
                    2. With <m>O</m> as center draw an arc of any radius to cut the line at <m>A</m>.With the same radius and <m>A</m> as center draw an arc to cut the previous arc at <m>B</m>.
                    </p>

                    <image source="/l5.png" width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                    <p>
                    3. Join <m>OB</m>. Measure angle <m>AOB</m>. Which angle have you constructed?
                    </p>

                    <image source="/l6.png" width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                    <p>
                    Expected observation.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        We get the required angle 
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <me>\angle AOB = 60^\circ</me>
                    </p>
                </statement>
             </activity>

             <example>
                <figure>
                    <caption></caption>
                    <interactive xml:id="geogebra-angle-60-2" geogebra="v59rdbd7" width="100%" aspect="9:5" reset-icon="yes" />
                 </figure>
             </example>

             <example>
                <figure>
