                    <interactive xml:id="geogebra-angle-60-3" geogebra="nrjepwry" width="100%" aspect="9:5" reset-icon="yes" />
                </figure>
             </example>
        </subsubsection>
        
        <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Constructing-angle-30">
            <title>Constructing <m>30^\circ</m></title>

                <figure>
                        <caption></caption>
                        <interactive xml:id="geogebra-angles-30" geogebra="meqbydqc" width="100%" aspect="9:5" reset-icon="yes" />
                </figure>
            <activity>
                <p>
                    Work in pairs
                </p>

                <p>
                    What you need: A ruler, a protractor and a pair of compasses.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Explore.
                </p>

                <p>
                    1.Construct <m>60^\circ</m> (as shown in the above activity).
                </p>

                <image source="/l6.png" width="40%">
                    <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                </image>

                <p>
                    2.With <m>A</m> as center, draw an arc of radius more than half of <m>AB</m> in the interior of <m>\angle AOB</m>. With the same radius and with <m>B</m> as center draw an arc to cut the previous one at <m>C</m>.
                </p>

                <p>
                    3.Join OC. Measure <m>\angle AOC</m>.
                </p>

                    <image source="/l7.png" width="40%">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                <p>
                Expected observation.
                </p>

                <p>
                    We get the required angle 
                </p>

                <p>
                    <me>\angle AOC = 30^\circ</me>
                </p>
          
            </activity>      
   </subsubsection>

